# qodana-js — Qodana Ultimate for JS/TS (image name = repoName). Feed code QDJS. Internal nightly dist
# feed: unsigned tar.gz, sha256-only (no GPG .asc), eap; the build mounts QODANA_READ_SPACE_PACKAGES_TOKEN
# (compose.private.yaml). The FIRST DHI-language-base image: QD_BASE_IMAGE is the dhi.io/node base
# (Node + Yarn PRE-BAKED), so there is NO NODE_MAJOR and no node toolchain. The node base ships a `node`
# user at uid 1000, so the qodana user shifts to 1001 via QODANA_UID/QODANA_GID — passed as COMPOSE BUILD
# ARGS (like clang's CLI_BASE_STAGE), NOT `.env` keys: dockerfile-x emits each INCLUDE_ARGS key as an
# `ARG NAME="val"` default, which the base fragment's own `ARG QODANA_UID=1000` (declared later, after the
# INCLUDE_ARGS block) would CLOBBER back to 1000 — verified empirically. A `--build-arg` always wins over a
# redeclared default, so the override lives in compose.yaml. eslint is pinned in
# lib/toolchain/eslint/package.json (renovate-tracked), NOT here. Pins in docs/phase-0-decisions.md;
# EnvContractTest asserts byte-identity for QD_VERSION/QD_BUILD/QD_PRODUCT_INFO_CODE + the feed/verify/eap
# contract and the node base digest.
QD_LINTER_SLUG=qodana-js
QD_VERSION=2026.3
QD_BUILD=263.146.1908
QD_RELEASE_TYPE=eap
QD_DISTRIBUTION_FEED=https://packages.jetbrains.team/files/p/sa/qodana-dist-internal/feed
QD_VERIFY_MODE=sha256
QD_PRODUCT_INFO_CODE=WS
QD_BASE_IMAGE=dhi.io/node:22-debian13-dev@sha256:e2df7b939a83d8825e7f5fcd8c9b54ecf53fd40565e5523d71a0442c7a098f10
CLI_BINARY=qodana
CLI_VERSION=2026.2
CLI_OS=linux
